Girl talk! These moments I never want to forget.

He turned 4 months on Christmas Eve! 
.
This wee lad is growing fast. Off the charts for length and head size and weighing in at 17lbs. 
.

#growingup_charlie
Bring on more snow!!!

My Lou Lou turned 3 yesterday and we made it as special as we could! This sweet and funny girl was spoiled rotten. She woke up to streamers and balloons and a string that lead her to her present! She requested a cat and dog cake and got to choose her favourite foods for each meal (waffles, Kraft dinner and lasagna). 
.
Our lives our so much brighter with this girl. She has a very strong personality and is so very kind. She has a bit of both her sisters in her and loves to stand out! She will tell stories and makes the room light up! I love you to bits little lady!
This was 2! Now bring on year 3
This guy has been loving his @charliecraneparis chair!!! So cozy and easy to assemble!!! Choose from a variety of colours and there is even Sherpa!!!!

The light just as it kisses the horizon to say “Goodnight”… 
.
It’s been so up and down with weather (storming, to rain to just blahhhh) and the sun has been hidden behind some gloomy skies for weeks now. Talk about your winter blues!!! I’m ready for the real winter to show up, and hell toss in a bit of sunshine please.
Come back snow I need you… we had a crazy epic storm and then this mild shit weather. This is not ok! Bring back the cold!!!
Going down memory lane 🥹 this little lady turns 6 this month…

I love the winter, and playing in the snow with my kids. Getting our gear on to go outside can be tricky… like I’m sweating buckets and I haven’t moved from the entryway. But when you dress appropriately and wear a abase layers like these from @natuerlich.goldig life is a-lot warmer outside! I’m obsessed with all these wool pieces and my kiddos love being warm!!!

Showing off this beautiful blanket by my sweet friend over @natuerlich.goldig 
.
Beautiful heirloom gifts for new mamas!!! 
.
Be sure to check my stories for a few of my favourite blanket cuddled baby pictures!!!!

It’s the simple things that have stuck out lately… with us being so sick just before Christmas and this little one taking the brunt of it… it’s been the little things. The moments of pure joy! 
.
I’m thankful for so much, but it’s our health that means the most. Our family is taking tiny steps to be healthier every day! Big changes can be hard so starting small and continuing with it can make just as big of an impact!!! 
.
Any healthy tips or lifestyle changes that you’ve made?? I want to hear them all!!! Even if ya think it’s nutty!

“A day without a nap for a baby is like a cupcake without frosting.” … unknown

Last official day being 5… birthdays are so hard now that I’m a parent. I remember when I was little excited to grow up and time never seemed to go by fast enough, loving my birthdays! Now I just want them to stay little and for time to slow down. 
.
On the flip side I do love watching them grow into these amazing little humans! With big hearts and big personalities!

This was 5…
My crazy, spontaneous, adventurous, lovable, cuddly Sweet T is one year older tomorrow. She has grown so much in one year almost catching up to her big sister! This one keeps me on my toes… she is so much like me it’s a bit freaky… love her big hear big laugh and big eyes!!!!

Happy Sixth Birthday to my little minion! We love you so much!

Molding our sons into responsible men can either be seen as a perilous journey or an opportunity to grow as a human being. On National Sons Day, we think about our boys and the legacy we leave behind as parents.  More than that, we take the time to listen to our boys — to hear their dreams or fears and thoughts on changing the world. We all have a role to play. Men and women. Educators. Professionals at all levels.

Sundays are made for chillin… but we have ringette, off to the arena we go! 
.
P.S. I played hockey all the way up to Varsity… so I just assumed my girls would play, here here I am a ringette mom! I never watched a ringette game in my life until last year after signing my girls up! I’m so impressed with how much focus is put into their skating. They have come so far and I’m one proud mama.

One I don’t remember if I shared. This was taken exactly 3 years ago when we were up north for 3 months living in isolation!!! She is all bundled up in my mom’s (her Nana’s) sweater. But something just struck me with this picture, and today I wanted something meaningful as we celebrate @kadebaileyphotography Her art is so moving I just wanted something appropriate to honour her! 
.

She is a poem. If you could speak her, the cadence would sound something like soft light in a dark hallway. It would move over you in waves, slowly at first, then build until you were embraced by the fullness of her sound. It would break your heart and heal it all at once and your breathe would catch in your throat as you whisper, “how lovely”. 

Today we celebrate our sweet friend @kadebaileyphotography as she hits 10k. Kade is someone who makes others feel seen, who’s work is gripping and emotive, and who embodies what it means to support and encourage those around her. Thank you for sharing your heart with us Kade. You really are such a light and an inspiration to us all. #kade_wecelebrateyou

So I saw my cousin @themagpiecakery post a beautiful pie picture today and found out it was Pie Day!!! I don’t bake many pies at my house (we are more cake and cookie people) so this is the closest I can come! 
.
If your looking for amazing baking ideas go check out Maggie @themagpiecakery she is not only an amazing baker but she has an eye for detail (also she was on the show Canada’s Next Baker) she also takes her own pictures for her masterpieces!!! AND she does online cooking classes sooooo basically it’s a one stop shop!!! 
. 
Happy Pie Day to all and to all a good night!!!

I remind my girls all the time that no matter what we are stuck together! Through the good and the bad my love stays the same! 
.
However when we leave this house we are not the most important people in others lives. They have their important people. We cannot force ourselves in their space! Some will welcome you in, others wont! And sometimes no matter how many times you knock or how many cookies you take over they just don’t want your company. And this is a hard one to swallow. 
I have to remind myself all the time that I cannot make everyone smile or happy even though my first instinct is humour… some just don’t find me funny and Welp that’s ok. But choosing kindness is what I choose! 
.

We are so in love with this fun casual set from @thesundaycollective_kids not only does it look freaking adorable (ps I want one in my size) but the quality is TipTop too! I love when I can feel good about the products my children wear. Knowing how they are made and the process behind the scenes. Understanding how our clothing is made is so important, and my kids loved learning about the process(link in stories). There is so much waste and I’m happy to share this earth friendly collection with you all today.
.
The TSC Naturals Collection used 100% natural resources that can safely be returned to the earth.
TSC Naturals are made with 100% GOTS Certified Organic Cotton and dyed with onions, indigo, and beechwood.
TSC Naturals are unisex styles coming in sizes 3y - 12y. Due to the seasonal materials used in the dying process, no two pieces will be exactly alike making them as unique as the kids who adorn them.

Battling a cancer diagnosis is hard, on so many levels. It can be overwhelming, challenging, fear-filled and lonely. What gives patients and families strength, though, is hope. There is always hope. September is childhood cancer awareness month. Childhood cancer is a harsh reality, affecting thousands of young lives every year. It’s crucial to raise awareness (not only this month, but always), support research, and provide hope for these brave young fighters. Together, we can make a difference! 🎗️💪

Childhood cancer has affected people we love and admire. @meg_nlo and her son are once again battling this awful disease, but Leo is strong and so is his family. Although Leo is in the thick of the battle, Meg has never stopped advocating for all children and families who are affected by this monster. Let’s all go gold and support the @thegoldhopeproject & @trucksofhope in honor of Leo, Meg, and all the other littles in our community who have unfairly had to go through this fight.

“A daughter is one of the most beautiful gifts this world has to give.” – Laurel Atherton

Today we celebrate daughters, whether you are someone’s daughter or have a daughter of your own. In this age of technology, with ubiquitous airbrushed images of “perfect” women, we teach our daughters that true beauty comes from the heart. In a society that values men’s contributions more than women’s, we teach our daughters to work harder and smarter. In a confusing world of mixed messages & questionable societal morals, we teach our daughters the wisdom to make intelligent choices.

Above all, we tell them every day how much they mean to us. To our beautiful daughters, always remember: you are beautiful, you are brave, you are capable, and you can accomplish anything. #togdaughters23

I will eventually get a birthday image posted…. I have not edited a thing this year (kinda killin me). 
.
I miss being creative, but between sicknesses, birthday month and back to school I’m a bit burnt out…it’s hard sometimes! Finding time for myself doesn’t come easy! I see so many others on here being creative, being a mom and I know it’s not a race, but man this race horse is tired and a bit jealous of her fellow racers (who in fact have no idea they are racing…). So I’m here to remind myself it’s not a race. I need to just do me, and if I’m not 💯 everyday that’s ok! My kids just need me even if it’s just lying in the floor being a hairdressers client of a doctor patient… they don’t give a hoot if I’m not 💯 they love me no matter what! So I’m posting this to be reminded, and if you need it too share away!
